Section 1:
1 L.D. 1516
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 HOUSING AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1000, L.D. 1516, “An Act to Strengthen
10 the Maine Development Foundation”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 1, 2 and 3.
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment removes from the bill the provisions authorizing the Director of the
1166 Bureau of General Services within the Department of Administrative and Financial
1177 Services to waive the competitive bidding requirement if the procurement of goods or
1188 services is consistent with the purposes and duties of the Maine Development Foundation
1199 and procuring those goods or services from the Maine Development Foundation is the most
2200 economical, effective and appropriate means of fulfilling a demonstrated need. The
2211 amendment retains the provision in the bill that revises the term limits of the Board of
2222 Directors of the Maine Development Foundation.
Page 1 - 132LR0991(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
